I'm curious, what is the
relevance of adjusting this clock

00:10:31.540 --> 00:10:35.070
from a little bit longer
than 24 hours to 24 hours?

00:10:35.070 --> 00:10:36.490
I mean, it seems like a small difference,

00:10:36.490 --> 00:10:40.040
24 hours and 40 minutes or 24 hours.

00:10:40.040 --> 00:10:42.470
Like what's the relevance?

00:10:42.470 --> 00:10:44.430
I mean, why should we care
about that short difference?

00:10:44.430 --> 00:10:45.440
- So, let's do the math.

00:10:45.440 --> 00:10:47.590
If you shift out .2 hours a day,

00:10:47.590 --> 00:10:49.560
in five days you're shifting out one hour.

00:10:49.560 --> 00:10:52.180
So you're literally one hour off

00:10:52.180 --> 00:10:54.530
in your social behavior in five days.

00:10:54.530 --> 00:10:56.590
In 10 days, you're two hours off.

00:10:56.590 --> 00:10:59.620
And if you're an organism
that is living in the wild,

00:10:59.620 --> 00:11:02.140
shifting out of the
right phase of the cycle,

00:11:02.140 --> 00:11:04.950
you could either miss food
or you could become food.

00:11:04.950 --> 00:11:07.070
So it's really essential for survival.

00:11:07.070 --> 00:11:10.630
I think it's one of the
strongest aspect of survival

00:11:10.630 --> 00:11:13.710
for animals to have the anticipation

00:11:13.710 --> 00:11:16.490
and the adjustment to the solar cycle.

00:11:16.490 --> 00:11:17.970
- And for humans as well.

00:11:17.970 --> 00:11:20.080
